CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Baltimore City – Stop Sign Monitoring Systems – Authorization of Pilot
3 Program
4 FOR the purpose of authorizing the use of stop sign monitoring systems in certain school
5 zones in Baltimore City, if authorized by local law; providing that the owner or driver
6 of a motor vehicle recorded failing to obey a stop sign is subject to a citation and a
7 certain civil penalty under certain circumstances; establishing certain defenses to a
8 charge of an alleged violation recorded by a stop sign monitoring system; prohibiting
9 a contractor administering a stop sign monitoring system from being compensated
10 in a certain manner; requiring that a certain percentage of the fines collected under
11 this Act be distributed to the local management board for Baltimore City and be used
12 only for certain purposes; and generally relating to the use of stop sign monitoring
13 systems in Baltimore City.
